A: The value of the linear correlation coefficient, r, is a numerical measure of the strength of the linear relationship between two variables. This value is calculated using the following formula: r = \frac{ \sum (x - \bar{x}) (y - \bar{y}) }{ \sqrt{ \sum (x - \bar{x})^2} \sqrt{ \sum (y - \bar{y})^2} }
